    }
    source: CORTEX_STEP_SOURCE_USER_EXPLICIT
    source_trajectory_step_info {
      trajectory_id: "9cce0c41-3d66-40b2-a74c-631bac0bdce9"
      step_index: 1
      cascade_id: "9cce0c41-3d66-40b2-a74c-631bac0bdce9"
    }
  }
  user_input {
    user_response: "You are a Principal Software Architect, Senior Full Stack Engineer, Data Engineer, DevOps Engineer, and Analytics Platform Architect.\n\nBuild a production-quality Healthcare Analytics Simulation Platform whose primary purpose is to generate realistic healthcare operational data for analytics, reporting, data engineering, and Databricks experimentation.\n\nThe application should NOT be a simple hospital management system.\n\nIts purpose is to continuously generate realistic healthcare business data that can later be ingested into Databricks for:\n\n* Data Engineering\n* ETL Pipelines\n* Delta Lake\n* Medallion Architecture\n* Data Warehousing\n* Analytics\n* Dashboarding\n* Machine Learning\n* Governance\n* Cost Optimization\n* Security Testing\n\nThe application must be fully functional and deployable using Docker.\n\n---\n\n# Primary Goal\n\nCreate a healthcare analytics platform that continuously produces realistic demo data automatically.\n\nThe system should simulate the daily operations of a medium-sized hospital network.\n\nThe generated data should resemble real-world healthcare business data but must never contain actual patient information.\n\nAll generated data must be synthetic.\n\n---\n\n# Technical Stack\n\nFrontend:\n\n* React\n* TypeScript\n* Vite\n* TailwindCSS\n* Recharts\n\nBackend:\n\n* Node.js\n* Express\n* TypeScript\n\nDatabase:\n\n* PostgreSQL\n\nInfrastructure:\n\n* Docker\n* Docker Compose\n\nTesting:\n\n* Jest\n* React Testing Library\n\nCI/CD Ready Structure\n\n---\n\n# Core Modules\n\n## Dashboard\n\nDisplay:\n\n* Total Patients\n* Active Patients\n* Daily Appointments\n* Revenue\n* Department Performance\n* Doctor Utilization\n* Patient Satisfaction\n* Appointment Trends\n\n---\n\n## Patient Module\n\nGenerate synthetic patients automatically.\n\nFields:\n\n* Patient ID\n* Name\n* Age\n* Gender\n* Blood Group\n* City\n* State\n* Registration Date\n* Insurance Provider\n* Patient Category\n\nPatient records should be automatically generated every few minutes.\n\n---\n\n## Appointment Module\n\nGenerate appointments automatically.\n\nFields:\n\n* Appointment ID\n* Patient ID\n* Doctor ID\n* Department\n* Appointment Date\n* Duration\n* Status\n* Revenue Generated\n\nGenerate:\n\n* Scheduled\n* Completed\n* Cancelled\n* Rescheduled\n\nappointments.\n\n---\n\n## Doctor Module\n\nGenerate doctors.\n\nFields:\n\n* Doctor ID\n* Name\n* Department\n* Experience\n* Consultation Fee\n* Utilization %\n\n---\n\n## Department Module\n\nDepartments:\n\n* Cardiology\n* Neurology\n* Orthopedics\n* Pediatrics\n* Emergency\n* Oncology\n* Dermatology\n* Radiology\n\nGenerate department-level KPIs.\n\n---\n\n## Billing Module\n\nGenerate:\n\n* Consultation Revenue\n* Lab Revenue\n* Pharmacy Revenue\n* Insurance Claims\n\nFields:\n\n* Transaction ID\n* Amount\n* Payment Type\n* Insurance Coverage\n* Department\n\n---\n\n# Analytics Data Generation Engine\n\nCreate a background scheduler.\n\nUse:\n\n* node-cron\n\nor equivalent.\n\nEvery 5 minutes:\n\nGenerate:\n\n* New Patients\n* New Appointments\n* Revenue Transactions\n* Department Metrics\n\nThe scheduler should continuously populate the database.\n\nData should gradually grow over time.\n\nThe goal is to create historical datasets suitable for Databricks analytics.\n\n---\n\n# Databricks Simulation Requirements\n\nThe generated data should be suitable for:\n\n## Bronze Layer\n\nRaw operational data.\n\nTables:\n\n* patients\n* appointments\n* doctors\n* departments\n* transactions\n\n---\n\n## Silver Layer\n\nCleaned and transformed data.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Patient Revenue Summary\n* Department Metrics\n* Doctor Performance Metrics\n\n---\n\n## Gold Layer\n\nBusiness reporting datasets.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Monthly Revenue\n* Department Profitability\n* Appointment Trends\n* Patient Growth\n* Insurance Utilization\n\nDesign database schema accordingly.\n\n---\n\n# Analytics Dashboard\n\nCreate visualizations for:\n\n* Revenue Trends\n* Appointments per Department\n* Patient Registrations\n* Insurance Utilization\n* Satisfaction Scores\n* Doctor Performance\n* Appointment Completion Rates\n\nUse Recharts.\n\n---\n\n# Security Requirements\n\nImplement:\n\n* JWT Authentication\n* Role-Based Access Control\n\nRoles:\n\n* Admin\n* Doctor\n* Analyst\n* Finance\n\nRestrict access accordingly.\n\n---\n\n# API Requirements\n\nCreate REST APIs for:\n\nPatients\n\nAppointments\n\nDoctors\n\nDepartments\n\nTransactions\n\nAnalytics\n\nMetrics\n\nHealth Check\n\n---\n\n# DevOps Requirements\n\nProject must include:\n\n* Dockerfile\n* Docker Compose\n* Environment Variables\n* Health Checks\n* Structured Logging\n* GitHub Actions CI Pipeline\n\nPipeline should:\n\n* Install Dependencies\n* Run Tests\n* Build Application\n* Build Docker Images\n\n---\n\n# Observability\n\nInclude:\n\n* Request Logging\n* Error Logging\n* Metrics Endpoint\n\nExpose:\n\n/health\n\n/metrics\n\nfor future Prometheus integration.\n\n---\n\n# Data Export Capability\n\nCreate APIs to export data as:\n\n* CSV\n* JSON\n\nThis is important because the exported data will later be ingested into Databricks.\n\n---\n\n# Seed Volume\n\nInitial seed should generate:\n\n* 10,000 Patients\n* 50,000 Appointments\n* 100,000 Transactions\n\nAfter deployment the scheduler should continue generating additional records automatically.\n\n---\n\n# Deliverables\n\nGenerate:\n\n1. Complete Folder Structure\n2. Database Schema\n3. Backend Code\n4. Frontend Code\n5. Docker Configuration\n6. Docker Compose\n7. GitHub Actions Workflow\n8. Cron-Based Data Generator\n9. README with Setup Instructions\n\nCode should be production-quality, modular, scalable, and suitable for demonstrating Databricks CI/CD, Pricing, Security, Governance, and Analytics capabilities.\n"
    items {
      text: "You are a Principal Software Architect, Senior Full Stack Engineer, Data Engineer, DevOps Engineer, and Analytics Platform Architect.\n\nBuild a production-quality Healthcare Analytics Simulation Platform whose primary purpose is to generate realistic healthcare operational data for analytics, reporting, data engineering, and Databricks experimentation.\n\nThe application should NOT be a simple hospital management system.\n\nIts purpose is to continuously generate realistic healthcare business data that can later be ingested into Databricks for:\n\n* Data Engineering\n* ETL Pipelines\n* Delta Lake\n* Medallion Architecture\n* Data Warehousing\n* Analytics\n* Dashboarding\n* Machine Learning\n* Governance\n* Cost Optimization\n* Security Testing\n\nThe application must be fully functional and deployable using Docker.\n\n---\n\n# Primary Goal\n\nCreate a healthcare analytics platform that continuously produces realistic demo data automatically.\n\nThe system should simulate the daily operations of a medium-sized hospital network.\n\nThe generated data should resemble real-world healthcare business data but must never contain actual patient information.\n\nAll generated data must be synthetic.\n\n---\n\n# Technical Stack\n\nFrontend:\n\n* React\n* TypeScript\n* Vite\n* TailwindCSS\n* Recharts\n\nBackend:\n\n* Node.js\n* Express\n* TypeScript\n\nDatabase:\n\n* PostgreSQL\n\nInfrastructure:\n\n* Docker\n* Docker Compose\n\nTesting:\n\n* Jest\n* React Testing Library\n\nCI/CD Ready Structure\n\n---\n\n# Core Modules\n\n## Dashboard\n\nDisplay:\n\n* Total Patients\n* Active Patients\n* Daily Appointments\n* Revenue\n* Department Performance\n* Doctor Utilization\n* Patient Satisfaction\n* Appointment Trends\n\n---\n\n## Patient Module\n\nGenerate synthetic patients automatically.\n\nFields:\n\n* Patient ID\n* Name\n* Age\n* Gender\n* Blood Group\n* City\n* State\n* Registration Date\n* Insurance Provider\n* Patient Category\n\nPatient records should be automatically generated every few minutes.\n\n---\n\n## Appointment Module\n\nGenerate appointments automatically.\n\nFields:\n\n* Appointment ID\n* Patient ID\n* Doctor ID\n* Department\n* Appointment Date\n* Duration\n* Status\n* Revenue Generated\n\nGenerate:\n\n* Scheduled\n* Completed\n* Cancelled\n* Rescheduled\n\nappointments.\n\n---\n\n## Doctor Module\n\nGenerate doctors.\n\nFields:\n\n* Doctor ID\n* Name\n* Department\n* Experience\n* Consultation Fee\n* Utilization %\n\n---\n\n## Department Module\n\nDepartments:\n\n* Cardiology\n* Neurology\n* Orthopedics\n* Pediatrics\n* Emergency\n* Oncology\n* Dermatology\n* Radiology\n\nGenerate department-level KPIs.\n\n---\n\n## Billing Module\n\nGenerate:\n\n* Consultation Revenue\n* Lab Revenue\n* Pharmacy Revenue\n* Insurance Claims\n\nFields:\n\n* Transaction ID\n* Amount\n* Payment Type\n* Insurance Coverage\n* Department\n\n---\n\n# Analytics Data Generation Engine\n\nCreate a background scheduler.\n\nUse:\n\n* node-cron\n\nor equivalent.\n\nEvery 5 minutes:\n\nGenerate:\n\n* New Patients\n* New Appointments\n* Revenue Transactions\n* Department Metrics\n\nThe scheduler should continuously populate the database.\n\nData should gradually grow over time.\n\nThe goal is to create historical datasets suitable for Databricks analytics.\n\n---\n\n# Databricks Simulation Requirements\n\nThe generated data should be suitable for:\n\n## Bronze Layer\n\nRaw operational data.\n\nTables:\n\n* patients\n* appointments\n* doctors\n* departments\n* transactions\n\n---\n\n## Silver Layer\n\nCleaned and transformed data.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Patient Revenue Summary\n* Department Metrics\n* Doctor Performance Metrics\n\n---\n\n## Gold Layer\n\nBusiness reporting datasets.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Monthly Revenue\n* Department Profitability\n* Appointment Trends\n* Patient Growth\n* Insurance Utilization\n\nDesign database schema accordingly.\n\n---\n\n# Analytics Dashboard\n\nCreate visualizations for:\n\n* Revenue Trends\n* Appointments per Department\n* Patient Registrations\n* Insurance Utilization\n* Satisfaction Scores\n* Doctor Performance\n* Appointment Completion Rates\n\nUse Recharts.\n\n---\n\n# Security Requirements\n\nImplement:\n\n* JWT Authentication\n* Role-Based Access Control\n\nRoles:\n\n* Admin\n* Doctor\n* Analyst\n* Finance\n\nRestrict access accordingly.\n\n---\n\n# API Requirements\n\nCreate REST APIs for:\n\nPatients\n\nAppointments\n\nDoctors\n\nDepartments\n\nTransactions\n\nAnalytics\n\nMetrics\n\nHealth Check\n\n---\n\n# DevOps Requirements\n\nProject must include:\n\n* Dockerfile\n* Docker Compose\n* Environment Variables\n* Health Checks\n* Structured Logging\n* GitHub Actions CI Pipeline\n\nPipeline should:\n\n* Install Dependencies\n* Run Tests\n* Build Application\n* Build Docker Images\n\n---\n\n# Observability\n\nInclude:\n\n* Request Logging\n* Error Logging\n* Metrics Endpoint\n\nExpose:\n\n/health\n\n/metrics\n\nfor future Prometheus integration.\n\n---\n\n# Data Export Capability\n\nCreate APIs to export data as:\n\n* CSV\n* JSON\n\nThis is important because the exported data will later be ingested into Databricks.\n\n---\n\n# Seed Volume\n\nInitial seed should generate:\n\n* 10,000 Patients\n* 50,000 Appointments\n* 100,000 Transactions\n\nAfter deployment the scheduler should continue generating additional records automatically.\n\n---\n\n# Deliverables\n\nGenerate:\n\n1. Complete Folder Structure\n2. Database Schema\n3. Backend Code\n4. Frontend Code\n5. Docker Configuration\n6. Docker Compose\n7. GitHub Actions Workflow\n8. Cron-Based Data Generator\n9. README with Setup Instructions\n\nCode should be production-quality, modular, scalable, and suitable for demonstrating Databricks CI/CD, Pricing, Security, Governance, and Analytics capabilities.\n"
    }
  }
