    thinking: "**Defining the Core Purpose**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on defining the core purpose of this platform. It needs to generate extremely realistic operational healthcare data. This data will then fuel analytics, reporting, data engineering tasks and Databricks experimentation. The scope is massive, a truly full-stack application.\n\n\n**Analyzing Available Skills**\n\nI\'ve been analyzing the available skills, specifically focusing on database capabilities. I\'m trying to determine the best approach for a PostgreSQL database within our Cloud Run environment. Considering `cloudsql-setup`, `cloudsql-execute-sql`, and `cloudsql-update-schema`, I\'m evaluating if Cloud SQL is feasible or if we\'ll rely on a mock or fallback database solution. I\'m exploring the implications of Docker support and how it affects database integration.\n\n\n"
