  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I have built the **Healthcare Analytics Simulation Platform** with full production-grade specifications, container orchestration, role-based workflows, and ingestion telemetry ready for Databricks.\n\nHere is a summary of the accomplishments and the design concepts applied to the application:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Experience Architecture\n* **Executive Slate & Calming Accent Placements**: Modeled around a professional, clean enterprise panel using high-contrast deep charcoal margins (`slate-900`) contrasted with warm clinical light panels (`slate-50`). \n* **Dynamic Real-Time Growth Telemetry**: Setup with automated background tick polling inside React, letting administrators watch metrics counters increment in real-time as simulation records are ingested dynamically.\n\n### \342\232\231\357\270\217 Core Technical Modules\n1. **Relational Generation & Seeding Engine (`server/database.ts`)**: Generates an initial realistic dataset of **10,000 deep clinical patients**, **50,005 doctors appointments spread over 12 months (inbound schedules, completions, and cancellations)**, and **100,000 detailed transactions** mimicking consultation fees, emergency triage services, lab diagnostics, and pharmacy dispensations.\n2. **Speed-Variable Ingestion Schedule**: Features a dynamic background event schedule loop. Users can configure simulation rates (Live, 10x Speed, 50x Speed, Paused) to trigger live data bursts on demand.\n3. **Medallion Pipeline & Aggregation Broker**:\n   * **Bronze Stage**: Append-only log arrays mapping raw patient registration records, schedules, and insurance transactions.\n   * **Silver Stage**: Demonstrates GDPR pass rates, parsing deduplications, and date-time coercion indicators showing a 99.85% schema compliance index.\n   * **Gold Stage**: Provides down-stream aggregations mapping insurance provider market share and monthly segmented revenue trends.\n4. **Interactive SQL Sandbox Playground**: Includes a live mock query interpreter where software engineers can select presets (such as top geriatric cardiology patient profiles or leading staff earners) or write custom `SELECT *` commands which dynamically inspect, filter, and tabulate memory databases on-the-fly.\n5. **Databricks PySpark Template Builders**: Generates copy-paste optimal PySpark and SQL scripts to stream or append raw CSV export files right into a Databricks Job Cluster.\n6. **Prometheus Metrics Probe (`/metrics` & `/health`)**: Integrates structured node uptime and counter diagnostics for Prometheus scraping and Grafana tracking.\n\n### \360\237\233\241\357\270\217 Secure Role-Based Adaptions (RBAC)\nLog in with these pre-defined user profiles to experience unique workspace views and menu configurations:\n* **Admin** (`admin`, password `admin123`): Has privileges to manipulate simulation speeds, manually stream extra records, and trigger database-level wipes.\n* **Doctor** (`doctor`, password `doctor123`): Displays clinician calendars, active consult rates, and capacity utilisation meters.\n* **Analyst** (`analyst`, password `analyst123`): Monitors pipeline pass metrics, Spark script files, and queries the SQL Sandbox.\n* **Finance** (`finance`, password `finance123`): Breaks down CFO claim payouts, insurer ratios, and gross income columns.\n\n### \360\237\220\263 DevOps & Deployment Assets\n* **Production Dockerfile**: Implements a highly cached, multi-stage Node execution runner with automated dynamic `/health` check commands.\n* **Docker Compose Builder (`docker-compose.yml`)**: Configures port mappings (`3000:3000`), persistent volumes, and auto-restart flags.\n* **GitHub Actions Pipeline (`ci.yml`)**: Automatically triggers code testing, checks formatting, and builds active images.\n"
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
